cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the optimization and reconstruction of existing cellular networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure. Therefore, cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the business aspect and profit modeling of network slicing, which falls under the category of information theory and systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also addresses challenges related to security and resource allocation, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), respectively.
